[2026-07-07T04:41:47.002Z] [INFO] [stderr] +### 12.1 Before You Start
[2026-07-07T04:41:47.002Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-07T04:41:47.002Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-07T04:41:47.002Z] [INFO] [stderr] +## 12. Tips for New AI Agents
[2026-07-07T04:41:47.002Z] [INFO] [stderr] +- [ ] Existing tests still pass
[2026-07-07T04:41:47.002Z] [INFO] [stderr] +- **Check the docs** — Documentation in `docs/` is the source of truth for architecture and conventions.
[2026-07-07T04:41:47.002Z] [INFO] [stderr] +- **Know the blast radius** — Before changing a function, check its callers. A small change can break many consumers.
[2026-07-07T04:41:47.002Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-07T04:41:47.002Z] [INFO] [stderr] +### 12.2 While Making Changes
[2026-07-07T04:41:47.002Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-07T04:41:47.002Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-07T04:41:47.002Z] [INFO] [stderr] +- **One thing at a time** — Make one logical change, validate it, then move to the next.
[2026-07-07T04:41:47.002Z] [INFO] [stderr] +- **Use types as guardrails** — Strict TypeScript will catch many mistakes at compile time. Let it.
[2026-07-07T04:41:47.002Z] [INFO] [stderr] +- **Mirror, don't invent** — If adding a new feature, copy the structure and naming of an existing feature.
[2026-07-07T04:41:47.002Z] [INFO] [stderr] +- **Always read first** — Understand the code before editing it. CodeGraph makes this fast.
[2026-07-07T04:41:47.002Z] [INFO] [stderr] +### 12.3 After Making Changes
[2026-07-07T04:41:47.002Z] [INFO] [stderr] +- **Check with `git diff`** — Review your changes before reporting completion to catch unintended modifications.
[2026-07-07T04:41:47.002Z] [INFO] [stderr] +- **Run validation early** — Run `typecheck` and `test` before making changes to confirm a healthy baseline.
[2026-07-07T04:41:47.002Z] [INFO] [stderr] +- **Keep changes minimal** — Prefer surgical edits over rewrites. Smaller diffs are safer and easier to review.
[2026-07-07T04:41:47.002Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-07T04:41:47.002Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-07T04:41:47.002Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-07T04:41:47.002Z] [INFO] [stderr] +- **Report clearly** — Tell the user what changed, why, and what validation passed.
[2026-07-07T04:41:47.002Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-07T04:41:47.002Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| Pitfall | How to Avoid |
[2026-07-07T04:41:47.002Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| Making large multi-file changes at once | Break work into small, verifiable steps |
[2026-07-07T04:41:47.002Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| Editing files before understanding their role | Use `codegraph explore` first |
[2026-07-07T04:41:47.002Z] [INFO] [stderr] +|---------|-------------|
[2026-07-07T04:41:47.002Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-07T04:41:47.002Z] [INFO] [stderr] +### 12.4 Common Pitfalls to Avoid
[2026-07-07T04:41:47.002Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| Ignoring the blast radius | Always check callers before modifying public functions |
[2026-07-07T04:41:47.002Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| Modifying test expectations instead of fixing the real issue | Read the test to understand expected behavior |
[2026-07-07T04:41:47.002Z] [INFO] [stderr] +
[2026-07-07T04:41:47.002Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| Skipping validation between changes | Run `pnpm typecheck` after each logical step |
[2026-07-07T04:41:47.002Z] [INFO] [stderr]  ---
[2026-07-07T04:41:47.002Z] [INFO] [stderr] +| Adding dependencies without asking | Propose the dependency and explain why it is needed |
[2026-07-07T04:41:47.002Z] [INFO] [stderr]  
[2026-07-07T04:41:47.002Z] [INFO] [stderr] +- **Run the full validation suite** — Do not rely on a single check. Run typecheck, lint, and tests.
